<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-314-166  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 314 166.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  March 26 1990 n583 p16(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOD cites 'critical technologies'; U.S. beats Soviets in mostareas, behind Japan in five. (Department of Defense)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Department of Defense (DOD) releases its annual report oncritical technologies, the Critical Technologies Plan, whichCongress hopes will form the basis of a national technologystrategy.andP;  The report details the development of technologies theDOD and Department of Energy believe to be most critical toensuring the long-term superiority of US weapon systems.andP;  The listis divided into three priority subgroups: Group A, pervasivetechnologies; Group B, weapons systems enabling technologies; andGroup C, emerging technologies.andP;  The report states that the DODand DOE are spending over $3 billion funding 19 criticaltechnologies.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MilitaryTechnologyReportsUnited States. Department of DefenseWeaponsExpenditures.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Critical technologies list. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>